Boil @water{400%ml} in a #pot{} for the couscous. Add @vegetable stock{1%sachet}.

When boiling, remove from heat, stir in the @couscous{200%g} and pop a lid on the #pot{}. Leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Halve, peel and chop @onion{1/2}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Cut the @tomato{2}(cut into 1cm chunks).

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the pit. Cut into chunks. Scoop out the flesh with a #spoon{}.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Zest the @lime{1} then halve and juice the lime.

Finely chop @coriander{5%g}(finely chopped, stalks and all).

Place a pan (without oil) over high heat and toast the @pumpkin seeds{20%g} until they start to pop.

> TIP: If you're not a fan of blue cheese this salad will still be delicious without!

In a #large bowl{}, make a vinaigrette by mixing together @oil{2%tbsp}, @balsamic vinegar{1%sachet} and @honey{1%sachet}.

Add 1 tsp lime juice and ½ tsp zest.

Mix the couscous and the chopped onion through the vinaigrette.

Carefully mix in the tomato, avocado, chopped coriander and @salad leaves{40%g}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the couscous between your plates.

Crumble the @blue cheese{55%g} on top.

Garnish with the pumpkin seeds.